Contains:    

   c_and_pl.txt   An introduction on integrating C and Prolog, with some
                  background on Prolog that indicates which parts of an
                  application are best coded in Prolog, and which in C.
                  (An expanded version of a Dr. Dobbs article, Aug 1994.)

   fun_w_pl.txt   Some fun applications of Prolog, adventure, OOP, 
                  animals and taxes. (First appeared in PC AI.)

   hello.txt      Technical note on how to implement the canonical hello
                  program from the supported environments of the Logic
                  Server API.

   logicsrv.txt   Overview notes on the design of the Cogent Prolog
                  API. (First appeared in PC AI Vendor's forum, Jul/Aug 1994.)

   obj_kbs.txt    Article about integrating objects with knowledge
                  bases.  (From Object Magazine).

   taxes_pl.txt   A description of a tax application written in Prolog.
                  It stresses the natural mapping between tax code and 
                  Prolog code.

   windows.txt    A brief introduction on how to extend Cogent Prolog
                  with MS-Windows GUI elements (includes code examples).

